nches and Updates (February 2025)\n\n### **JetBrains AI Tools - Free Tier Announced**\nJetBrains announced a free AI assistant tier that is being rolled out with their 2025.1 update. The toolset is being integrated across their development environment ecosystem.\n\n### **Microsoft AI Developer Tools**\nFrom the Microsoft AI Developer Day events (December 17, 2025), several tools were highlighted:\n- **GitHub Copilot Coding Agent** - Advanced autonomous coding capabilities\n- **VS Code 1.07** - Latest version with enhanced AI features\n- **Visual Studio 2026** - Intelligent development environment\n- **GitHub Copilot CLI** - Command-line interface AI assistant\n- **Plan Agent & Custom Agent** in GitHub Copilot\n\n### **Anthropic Claude Code**\nReleased in February 2025:\n- Official command-line AI programming tool\n- Runs in terminal environment\n- Completes code generation, refactoring, and debugging through natural language\n- Version 2.1 released in February 2026, upgraded to \"agent operating system\"\n\n### **Chinese Market Developments**\nSeveral AI coding tools and updates mentioned:\n- **Trae** (ByteDance) - Localized Chinese tool gaining traction\n- **CodeArts AI** (Huawei) - Enterprise-focused with private deployment\n- **AI Coder** (Alibaba Cloud) - Full-stack coverage\n- Various models enhancing coding capabilities including GLM-5, MiniMax M2.5\n\n### **Key Trends in AI Developer Tools for 2025**\n\nThe search results indicate that AI developer tools are evolving from \"coding assistants\" to \"intelligent development partners\" with:\n- Multi-modal interaction (voice + gesture control planned)\n- Autonomous debugging and bug fixing\n- Full workflow automation from requirements to deployment\n- Enhanced security with zero-trust architecture\n- Specialized modules for vertical domains (autonomous driving, quantum computing)\n\n**Note:** The searches didn't return specific results with the exact phrase \"launched this week\" - most results covered broader timeframes in February 2025 or were retrospective pieces about 2025 developments. For the most current weekly launches, I'd recommend checking tech news sites like TechCrunch, The Verge, or Product Hunt directly.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
