title\":\"追踪GitHub Trending 热门项目，提供历史Star/Commit 趋势和 ...\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/Lilembas/detailed-github-trending\"},{\"title\":\"claude code\",\"url\":\"https://m.blog.csdn.net/tqs_123456/article/details/157019341\"},{\"title\":\"AI CLI / Plugins / Extension 应用从小白到大师\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnblogs.com/treasury-manager/p/19131789\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code 从入门到精通：最全配置指南和工具推荐\",\"url\":\"https://segmentfault.com/a/1190000047256519?utm_source=sf-similar-article\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code CLI 使用文档 (2025 最新版)\",\"url\":\"https://blog.csdn.net/come11234/article/details/156422496\"}]\n\nBased on my search, here's what I found about the **Claude Code CLI release announcement**:\n\n## Initial Release - February 2025\n\nClaude Code was initially announced as a **research preview** on **February 24, 2025**, as part of the Claude 3.7 Sonnet release. According to the search results:\n\n- It was introduced quietly as the second item in the Claude 3.7 Sonnet announcement\n- Released as a **limited research preview** available to a restricted number of users on a \"first-come, first-served\" basis\n- Anthropic described it as \"an agentic command line tool\" for agentic coding\n\n## General Availability - May 22, 2025\n\nAfter months of preview testing, Claude Code was officially made **generally available (GA)** on May 22, 2025, coinciding with the release of Claude 4 models (Opus 4 and Sonnet 4).\n\nKey announcements included:\n- **IDE Extensions**: Beta versions for VS Code and JetBrains\n- **Claude Code SDK**: Released for TypeScript and Python, allowing developers to build their own agents\n- **Direct Integration**: Claude Code could run in terminals, IDEs, or via SDK in the background\n\n## What is Claude Code?\n\nClaude Code is Anthropic's **official CLI tool** for agentic coding that:\n- Runs directly in the terminal\n- Understands entire codebases through agentic search\n- Can edit files, write and run tests, commit and push code to GitHub\n- Uses command-line tools with user authorization\n- Supports natural language commands for programming tasks\n\n## Key Milestones\n\n- **Feb 2025**: Research preview launch\n- **May 22, 2025**: General availability with Claude 4 release\n- **June 2025**: SDK release, MCP support, and custom hooks\n- **September 2025**: v2.0 release with UI upgrades and VS Code plugin\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific details about any particular aspect of the release?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
