laude 3.7\n- Capable of browsing codebases, writing and running tests, and even autonomously submitting changes to GitHub\n- Can write code, execute it, check results, and iterate further\n\n**3. Performance Improvements**\n- Achieved industry-leading performance on coding and complex reasoning benchmarks\n- SWE-Bench test accuracy reached **62.3%**\n- Significantly improved performance in mathematics, coding, and other tasks\n- Described as \"their most intelligent model to date\"\n\n### Notable Context:\n\nThe version jump from Claude 3.5 to 3.7 (skipping 3.6) occurred because Anthropic released a major upgrade to Claude 3.5 Sonnet in October 2024 but kept the same name, leading the developer community to unofficially call the unnamed \"3.5 Sonnet v2\" as \"3.6\". This resulted in Anthropic effectively skipping a version number.\n\nThe model features a unique \"hybrid reasoning\" architecture that combines rapid intuitive responses with deep step-by-step reasoning capabilities, making it particularly well-suited for complex programming and professional domain tasks.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
