      "I found several relevant search results about AI tools for code debugging, refactoring, and testing. Here's a summary of the key findings:\n\n## **AI Debugging Tools**\n\n### Debug-gym (Microsoft Research)\n- **Purpose**: An environment designed to teach AI coding tools how to debug code like programmers\n- **Key Insight**: Developers spend most of their time debugging rather than writing code\n- **Capability**: AI tools can propose fixes for hundreds of open issues, with developers simply approving them before merging\n\n### JetBrains AI Assistant (2026)\n- **Features**: Deep integration with IDE debugger for intelligent debugging\n- **Capability**: Can analyze exception stack traces in real-time during breakpoint debugging\n- **Provides**: Possible error causes and fix suggestions based on current debugging context\n\n### JamGPT\n- **Type**: Chrome extension for AI-powered debugging\n- **Features**: \n  - Analyzes bug descriptions, browser/OS info, console logs, user actions, and network logs\n  - Integrates with GitHub repositories\n  - AI algorithms self-learn and optimize over time to provide more accurate fix suggestions\n\n## **AI Refactoring Tools**\n\n### JetBrains AI Assistant\n- **Specializes in**: Complex refactoring operations with project-level context awareness\n- **Capabilities**:\n  - Automatic class splitting, method extraction, and variable renaming\n  - Generates new classes and methods matching existing code patterns\n  - Understands code symbol links and dependencies to avoid post-refactoring conflicts\n\n### Blackbox AI\n- **Purpose**: Fast and clean tool for coding and refactoring\n- **Integration**: Works with AI-native IDEs like Cursor for quick edits and version control\n\n## **AI Testing Tools**\n\n### Automated Test Generation\n- **Function**: Analyzes code structure and execution paths to generate high-quality test cases\n- **Benefits**:\n  - Covers more boundary conditions and edge cases\n  - Automatically adjusts test cases based on code changes\n  - Uses machine learning to optimize test execution order, reducing testing time\n\n### AI-Driven Testing Systems\n- **Features**:\n  - Generates adaptive test cases\n  - Prioritizes the most critical tests\n  - Can predict errors based on historical data to help avoid future problems\n\n## **General AI Code Analysis Tools**\n\n### DeepCode\n- **Capabilities**:\n  - Real-time monitoring for potential errors during coding\n  - Detects syntax errors, logical errors, security vulnerabilities, and code structure issues\n  - Provides direct fix suggestions or automatic repairs for common errors\n\n### Additional Features\n- CI/CD pipeline integration\n- Enterprise-level project compliance support\n- Detailed detection reports for tracking problem resolution progress\n\nThese tools collectively represent the state of AI-assisted coding as of February 2026, with particular strength in debugging automation, intelligent refactoring, and adaptive testing generation."
