nts:\n- **AI-Driven CI/CD**: By 2026, AI-driven CI/CD tools (like GitHub Copilot for CI) are becoming popular, automatically generating pipeline configurations\n- **Automation Benefits**: AI can automate pipeline management, predict failures, and handle complex deployment workflows\n- **Kubernetes Integration**: AI tools are being used to generate Kubernetes deployment manifests and automate container orchestration\n\n### **AI Engineering & MLOps**\n- **CI/CD for ML**: MLOps practices include continuous integration/deployment specifically for machine learning systems\n- **Feature Stores**: Tools like Tecton or Feast for unified feature management\n- **Success Impact**: Gartner predicts that by 2026, enterprises adopting AI engineering practices will achieve 4x higher AI project success rates\n\n### **AI Operations (AIOps)**\n- **AI Operations Teams**: By 2026, specialized AI operations teams are expected to emerge, similar to existing DevOps practices\n- **Monitoring & Compliance**: Continuous model monitoring, drift prevention, cost control, and regulatory compliance management\n\n### **Industry Events**\n- **Microsoft Events**: AI-focused events scheduled for February 2026, including sessions on \"automated DevOps deployment\" and \"orchestration\" patterns\n- **Conferences**: Events like AgentCon and Model Mondays addressing AI agent orchestration\n\n---\n\n**Note**: Some search results appear to be from early 2026 or late 2025, suggesting this is a forward-looking topic with significant industry momentum. The AI orchestration and AI-driven CI/CD space appears to be rapidly evolving as enterprises seek better ways to manage and deploy AI systems at scale.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
