 `.beads/` directory with version control\n- **Zero conflicts**: Hash-based IDs (e.g., `bd-a1b2`) for multi-agent, multi-branch workflows\n- **Memory compression**: Semantic \"memory decay\" to summarize old tasks and save context window space\n- **Agent optimization**: JSON output, dependency tracking, auto-detection of executable tasks\n- **Stealth mode**: Can be used locally without committing to repository\n\n### Installation Methods:\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/steveyegge/beads/main/scripts/install.sh | bash\n# or\nnpm install -g @beads/bd\n# or\nbrew install steveyegge/beads/bd\n```\n\n### Recent Community Activity (February 2026):\nSeveral articles and tutorials were published in February 2026 about using Beads with Claude Code, including guides on multi-agent orchestration and Kanban UI integrations. The project has gained significant traction in the AI agent development community.\n\nSteve Yegge, formerly of Amazon, Google, and Grab (currently at Sourcegraph), built Beads in just 6 days using Claude himself, exemplifying \"Vibe Coding\" methodology.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
